content: Nice app, attractive design. Wondering if it would work better as a speedometer if I paired an external bluetooth gps unit capable of refreshing at 10 Hz?  Also, the average speed calculation is mysterious to me. Is it the average speed / time spent traveling or average speed / distance traveled? The reason I ask is, if you go for a walk for half an hour at 2 mph, and then travel in a car at a much greater speed, the "average speed" remains at a low value for an extended period of time. It seems to be that the calculation should be done by distance traveled. Just my two pennies....
replyContent:
Hi Paul, YES - it's works so much better with a 10Hz bluetooth receiver because it then has zero lag. It updates faster than the digital display in my old Honda Civic.
There are two settings for the average speed - the time spent moving or all-time since last reset. So however it counts the time used in the calculation it's still distance/time.
